The paper focuses on end-to-end learning strategies for 3D shape inference from images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a probabilistic inference-based reconstruction framework, which involves learning architectures and latent variable models, suggesting that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), graphics (cs.GR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions using Monte Carlo and variational approximation, which are common techniques in neural networks and probabilistic modeling (cs.NE).
